<p> <span style="font-size: small;">Week 1: Introduction to the course</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Week 2 &amp; 3 Unit: 1 History of Science and Technology</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Week 4-5: Unit 2: Communication</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Week 6-7: Unit 3: Energy</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Week 8-9: Unit 4: Robots &amp; Artificial Intelligence</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Week 10-11: Unit 5: Food Technology</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Week 12-13: Unit 6: The Internet</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Week 14: Revision</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Week 15: Test &amp; presentations</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Week 16: Test &amp; presentations</span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;"> </span></p>
<p> </p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の方法</div><div style="margin:10px"><p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><span style="font-size: small;">Grades</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Attendance &amp; participation: 15%</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Moodle Homework: 10%</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Weekly Quizzes: 15%</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Test: 40%</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Presentation: 20%</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;"> </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Based on a maximum score of 100, grades will be awarded as follows: S (Excellent) 90 - 100 A (Very good) 80-90 B (Good) 70-80 C (Pass) 60-70 D (Fail) Below 60.</span></p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の基準</div><div style="margin:10px">秀　 達成目標を超えた成果を上げている　100点～90点<br>優　 達成目標に十分達している　　　　　89点～80点<br>良　 達成目標に達している　　　　　　　79点～70点<br>可　 達成目標に概ね達している　　　　　69点～60点<br>不可 達成目標に達していない　　　　　　59点以下<br><p><strong>The teacher of each course will explain the grading system in class. Based on a maximum score of 100, grades will be awarded as follows: S (Excellent) 90 - 100 A (Very good) 80-90 B (Good) 70-80 C (Pass) 60-70 D (Fail) Below 60.</strong></p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">事前・事後学修等の指示及び履修にあたっての注意事項</div><div style="margin:10px"><p align="left"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong><em>Come to class on time!</em></strong></span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-size: small;">• If you enter the class more than 5 minutes late, you will be marked late. I will count three “lates” as one absence, so be sure to come to class on time.  If you are more than 30 minutes late you will be considered absent.  If you are absent five times you will fail the course.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-size: small;"> • You are responsible for coming to class prepared. Please do assigned homework/assignments at home.  <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">No late assignments will be accepted.</span></strong>  Also, points will be deducted for assignments/homework done in class.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-size: small;">• If you have any special needs (hearing, visual, etc.), please see me as soon as possible so we can make adjustments.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-size: small;"> • Please download the textbook sound files to your phone so that you can listen easily.</span></p>
<p align="left"><span style="font-size: small;"><span>事前学修：教科書や教材の予習，予習課題に取り組む。 （30 分）</span><br /><span>事後学修：授業内の講義や解説を理解し，事後課題（レポート，</span><span>プレゼンテーション，小テストなど）に取り組む。（30分）</span></span></p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">教科書</div><div style="margin:10px">Humanity & Technology (3rd edition) by Brian Cullen  <br></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">参考書</div><div style="margin:10px">Published by Intercom Press<br></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">オフィスアワー</div><div style="margin:10px"><p><span style="font-size: small;">Please contact me at landsberrysensei@gmail.com if you have any questions. Also, feel free to talk to me any time before and after class. </span></p></div></td></tr></table><p><span style="background-color:#ffffff;"><a href="https://cms7.ict.nitech.ac.jp/moodle40a/syllabus/search.php">検索 に戻る</a></span><p></center>